ferences between\nmeasured and expected source location was 1.82 mm. Dose deviations remained\nbelow 5% in all the explored measurement conditions. With regard to dwell time\nmeasurement accuracy, the maximum deviation observed at all distances was 0.56\ns. Conclusions: The performance of the system demonstrated that it could be\nused for real-time dose, position and dwell time measurements during HDR\nbrachytherapy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Oct 2019 08:56:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-27"}
